1,3:1,6 beta-glucans were determined with the Megazyme Mushroom and Yeast Test Kit (K-YBGL), using sulfuric acid for hydrolysis. The method involves quantification of glucose in acid-hydrolyzed samples after enzymatic digestion with exo-1,3-beta-glucanase and beta-glucosidase and subtraction of the contribution of glucose from alpha-glucans, free sucrose and glucose, as reported by McCleary and Draga (J AOAC Int. 2016 Mar-Apr;99(2):364-73). Results should be interpreted based on the assumptions inherent in the methodology, as well as the measurement uncertainty for individual samples (Percent relative standard deviation for sample replicates: 0.0-35.4, mean 9.1, median 6.5, n=24).
